{{Infobox university |image_name=Mayor Michael Bloomberg.jpg |image_size=200px |caption = [[Michael Bloomberg]] |name=Bloomberg Distinguished Professorships |established={{Start date|2013}} |campus= |website={{URL|http://web.jhu.edu/administration/provost/BDP}} }}
'''Bloomberg Distinguished Professorships''' (BDPs) were established as part of a $350 million investment by [[Michael Bloomberg]], [[JHU]] Class of 1964, to [[Johns Hopkins University]] in 2013. Fifty faculty members, ten from [[Johns Hopkins University]] and forty recruited from institutions worldwide, will be chosen for these endowed professorships based on their research, teaching, service, and leadership records.<ref>Barbaro, Michael. [https://www.nytimes.com/2013/01/27/nyregion/at-1-1-billion-bloomberg-is-top-university-donor-in-us.html?_r=0 "$1.1 Billion in Thanks From Bloomberg to Johns Hopkins"], ''[[The New York Times]]'', New York, 26 January 2013. Retrieved on 1 March 2015.</ref><ref name=anderson>Anderson, Nick. [https://www.washingtonpost.com/local/education/bloomberg-pledges-350-million-to-johns-hopkins-university/2013/01/26/9c0e1a5a-67d6-11e2-93e1-475791032daf_story.html " Bloomberg pledges $350 million to Johns Hopkins University "], ''[[The Washington Post]]'', Washington, D.C., 23 January 2013. Retrieved on 12 March 2015.</ref><ref>Associated Press [http://www.huffingtonpost.com/2013/01/27/michael-bloomberg-johns-hopkins_n_2563494.html "Michael Bloomberg's Contributions To Johns Hopkins University Top $1 Billion"], ''[[Huffington Post]]'', New York, 27 January 2013. Retrieved on 11 March 2015.</ref> The program is directed and managed by Johns Hopkins University Vice Provost for Research, Dr. [[Denis Wirtz]].<ref>[http://web.jhu.edu/administration/provost/BDP "Bloomberg Distinguished Professorships"]</ref>
== Purpose == The BDPs will create interdisciplinary connections and collaborations across [[Johns Hopkins University]], train and mentor undergraduate and graduate students, and strengthen the university's leadership in research fields of international interest.<ref name=anderson/><ref name="forbes.com">Mac, Ryan. [https://www.forbes.com/sites/ryanmac/2013/01/26/michael-bloomberg-pledges-350-to-johns-hopkins-takes-university-lifetime-giving-to-1-billion/ “Michael Bloomberg Pledges $350 Million To Johns Hopkins University"], ''[[Forbes]]'', New York, 26 January 2013. Retrieved on 12 March 2015.</ref><ref>Dance, Scott. [http://articles.baltimoresun.com/2013-01-26/news/bs-md-bloomberg-hopkins-donation-20130126_1_million-gift-public-health-school-johns-hopkins “Bloomberg donates $350 million to Johns Hopkins for research, scholarships"], ''[[The Baltimore Sun]]'', Baltimore, 26 January 2013. Retrieved on 2 March 2015.</ref> Each of the BDPs will be appointed in at least two divisions or disciplines.<ref>[http://philanthropynewsdigest.org/news/with-latest-350-million-gift-to-johns-hopkins-bloomberg-surpasses-1-billion-in-giving-to-alma-mater “With Latest $350 Million Gift to Johns Hopkins, Bloomberg Surpasses $1 Billion in Giving to Alma Mater"], ''Philanthropy News Digest'', New York, 29 January 2013. Retrieved on 10 March 2015.</ref><ref>Franklin, Frank. [http://usnews.nbcnews.com/_news/2013/01/27/16721478-nycs-mayor-bloomberg-giving-another-350-million-to-alma-mater-johns-hopkins?lite “NYC's Mayor Bloomberg giving another $350 million to alma mater Johns Hopkins"], ''[[NBC News]]'', New York, 27 January 2013. Retrieved on 1 March 2015.</ref>
== Timeline == As of May 2018, thirty three<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://hub.jhu.edu/2018/05/21/richard-huganir-bloomberg-distinguished-professor/|title=Renowned neuroscientist Richard Huganir named Bloomberg Distinguished Professor|date=2018-05-21|work=The Hub|access-date=2018-05-22|language=en}}</ref> of the fifty Bloomberg Distinguished Professorships have been announced.<ref name="forbes.com"/><ref name="releases.jhu.edu">Rosen, Jill. [http://releases.jhu.edu/2015/03/30/johns-hopkins-appoints-four-to-bloomberg-distinguished-professorships/ "Johns Hopkins Appoints Four to Bloomberg Distinguished Professorships"], "JH Press Release", Baltimore, 30 March 2015. Retrieved on 31 March 2015.</ref><ref name="ReferenceA">{{Cite web|url=http://hub.jhu.edu/2016/12/07/lisa-cooper-bloomberg-distinguished-professor/|title=Health equity researcher Lisa Cooper named 25th Bloomberg Distinguished Professor|last=7|first=Hub staff report / Published Dec|last2=2016|date=2016-12-07|website=The Hub|access-date=2016-12-07}}</ref>
The first cohort of scholars in 2014 included two [[Nobel Laureates]], [[Peter Agre]] and [[Carol W. Greider]], and poverty researcher, [[Kathryn Edin]].<ref>Brooks, Kelly. [http://hub.jhu.edu/2014/02/17/bloomberg-distinguished-professors "With Bloomberg Distinguished Professorships, Johns Hopkins aims to foster cross-specialty collaboration"], ''JHU Hub'', Baltimore, 27 February 2014. Retrieved on 1 March 2015.</ref> Sociologist Stephen Morgan, neuroscientist Patricia Janak, and organization theorist Kathleen Sutcliffe, were announced as the second group of BDPs in June 2014.<ref>Brooks, Kelly. [http://www.newswise.com/articles/johns-hopkins-appoints-three-to-bloomberg-distinguished-professorship-positions "Johns Hopkins Appoints Three to Bloomberg Distinguished Professorship Positions"], ''Newswise'', Charlottesville, 11 June 2014. Retrieved on 1 March 2015.</ref> In March 2015, it was announced that [[Health informatics|biomedical informatics]] expert [[Christopher G. Chute]] of the [[Mayo Clinic]] and [[Infection|infectious disease]] specialist [[Arturo Casadevall]] of the [[Albert Einstein College of Medicine]] would be joining [[Johns Hopkins University]] as BDPs.<ref>Newswise. [http://www.newswise.com/articles/albert-einstein-college-of-medicine-announces-new-chair-of-department-of-microbiology-immunology "Albert Einstein College of Medicine Announces New Chair of Department of Microbiology & Immunology"], "Newswise", Charlottesville, 30 December 2014. Retrieved on 23 March 2015.</ref><ref>Parmar, Arundhati. [https://www.minnpost.com/medcity-news/2011/12/50-best-mayo-clinic-doctors-ever "The 50 best Mayo Clinic doctors. Ever."], "[[MinnPost]]", Minneapolis, 22 December 2011. Retrieved 22 March 2015.</ref><ref>ANSI. [http://www.ansi.org/news_publications/news_story.aspx?menuid=7&articleid=58d72ebe-f2b4-425e-91bf-9bd0e7f6736e "People on the Move"], "[[American National Standards Institute]]", Washington DC, 21 November 2014. Retrieved on 22 March 2015.</ref> Two internally selected professors were also named BDPs: [[big data]] scientist [[Alex Szalay]] and [[Computational biology|computational biologist]] [[Steven Salzberg]].<ref name="releases.jhu.edu"/> In July 2015, four new Bloomberg Distinguished Professors were named across five divisions of [[Johns Hopkins University]]: global food ethicist and nutritionist Jessica Fanzo, [[biophysicist]] [[Taekjip Ha]], cell dynamics investigator [[Rong Li]], and [[computer vision]] specialist Alan Yuille.<ref name="Brooks, Kelly 2015">Brooks, Kelly. [http://hub.jhu.edu/2015/07/08/bloomberg-distinguished-professors-fanzo-ha-li-yuille "Four new Bloomberg Distinguished Professors named at Johns Hopkins"], ''JHU Hub'', Baltimore, 8 July 2015. Retrieved on 8 July 2015.</ref>
In October 2015, Paul Ferraro, an environmental economist was announced as a BDP<ref>Parsons, Tim. [http://carey.jhu.edu/news-and-views/paul-ferraro-named-bloomberg-distinguished-professor-for-carey-whiting "Paul Ferraro named Bloomberg Distinguished Professor at Johns Hopkins"], ''JHU HUB'', Baltimore, 21 October 2015. Retrieved 22 October 2015.</ref> and in November, it was announced that noted [[statistician]] [[Nilanjan Chatterjee]] would be joining Johns Hopkins as a BDP from the [[National Cancer Institute]].<ref>Messersmith, Julie. [http://hub.jhu.edu/2015/11/10/chatterjee-named-bloomberg-distinguished-professor "Nilanjan Chatterjee named Bloomberg Distinguished Professor at Johns Hopkins"], "JHU HUB", Baltimore, 10 November 2015. Retrieved on 11 November 2015.</ref> Experimental [[astrophysicist]] and [[cosmologist]] [[Charles L. Bennett]] and [[Epigenetics|epigeneticist]] Andrew Feinberg were named BDPs in December 2015.<ref>Messersmith, Julie. [http://hub.jhu.edu/2015/12/15/bloomberg-distinguished-professors-bennett-and-feinberg "JHU's Charles Bennett and Andrew Feinberg named Bloomberg Distinguished Professors"], ''JHU Hub'', Baltimore, 15 December 2016. Retrieved on 27 January 2016.</ref> In February 2016, it was announced that diabetes and obesity expert Rexford Ahima of the [[University of Pennsylvania]] was joining Johns Hopkins as a BDP<ref>Messersmith, Julie. [http://hub.jhu.edu/2016/02/23/rexford-ahima-named-bloomberg-distinguished-professor "Rexford Ahima named Bloomberg Distinguished Professor at Johns Hopkins"], ''JHU Hub'', Baltimore, 23 February 2016. Retrieved on 23 February 2016.</ref> and in April 2016 Mauro Maggioni of Duke University announced that he was joining Johns Hopkins as a BDP.<ref>Messersmith, Julie. [http://hub.jhu.edu/2016/04/14/mauro-maggioni-bloomberg-distinguished-professor "Big data scientist named 20th Bloomberg Distinguished Professor at Johns Hopkins"], ''JHU Hub'', Baltimore, 14 April 2016. Retrieved on 28 April 2016.</ref> In May 2016, it was announced that [[Computational biology|computational biologist]] Michael Schatz of the [[Cold Spring Harbor Laboratory]] was named the 21st Bloomberg Professor at Johns Hopkins.<ref>Messersmith, Julie. [http://hub.jhu.edu/2016/05/26/michael-schatz-bloomberg-distinguished-professor "Computational biologist Michael Schatz named 21st Bloomberg Professor at Johns Hopkins"], ''JHU Hub'', Baltimore, 26 May 2016. Retrieved on 26 May 2016.</ref> [[Nobel Prize in Physics|Nobel Laureate in Physics]] [[Adam Riess]], expert on chromatin biology and biochemistry [[Carl Wu]], and neuroscientist Ulrich Mueller were announced as BDPs in summer 2016.<ref name="hub.jhu.edu">Messersmith, Julie. [http://hub.jhu.edu/2016/07/08/adam-riess-bloomberg-distinguished-professor "Nobel laureate Adam Riess named 22nd Bloomberg Distinguished Professor at Johns Hopkins"], ''JHU Hub'', Baltimore, 8 July 2016. Retrieved on 13 July 2016.</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=http://hub.jhu.edu/2016/08/03/carl-wu-bloomberg-distinguished-professor/|title=Renowned scientist Carl Wu named Bloomberg Distinguished Professor at Johns Hopkins|last=7|first=Hub staff report / Published Dec|last2=2016|date=2016-08-03|website=The Hub|access-date=2016-12-07}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=http://hub.jhu.edu/2016/08/25/ulrich-mueller-bloomberg-distinguished-professor/|title=Neuroscientist Ulrich Mueller joins JHU as Bloomberg Distinguished Professor|last=7|first=Hub staff report / Published Dec|last2=2016|date=2016-08-25|website=The Hub|access-date=2016-12-07}}</ref> In December 2016, heath equity expert was named the 25th BDP, marking the halfway point of the program.<ref name="ReferenceA"/>
