{{polisci-stub}}

'''Christoph Gottfried Andreas Giebel''' (13 September 1820 – 14 November 1881) was a [[Germany|German]] [[zoologist]] and [[palaeontologist]].

==Biography==
Giebel was born on 13 September 1820 in [[Quedlinburg]], [[Prussian Saxony]], and educated at the [[University of Halle]], where he graduated in 1845 with a [[Ph.D.]]. At Halle his instructors were [[Ernst Friedrich Germar]] and [[Hermann Burmeister]].<ref>[http://www.deutsche-biographie.de/pnd116616660.html Giebel, Christoph Gottfried Andreas] Deutsche Biographie</ref> In 1858 he became professor of [[zoology]] and director of the museum there. He died on 14 November 1881 at [[Halle, Saxony-Anhalt|Halle]].{{sfn|Chisholm|1911}}
[[File:CGAGiebel 02.JPG|right|thumb|Memorial stone of Christoph Gottfried Giebel in Halle.]]
==Works==
Giebel's chief publications were ''Palaeozoologie'' (1846); ''Fauna der Vorwelt'' (1847-1856); ''Deutschlands Petrefacten'' (1852); ''Odontographie'' (1855); ''Lehrbuch der Zoologie'' (1857); ''Thesaurus ornithologiae'' (1872-1877).{{sfn|Chisholm|1911}} His 5-volume ''Naturgeschichte des Tierreichs'' (1859–1864) is considered to be a forerunner to ''[[Brehms Tierleben]]''.<ref>[http://www.catalogus-professorum-halensis.de/giebelchristiangottfried.html Christian Gottfried Giebel] Catalogus Professorum Halensis</ref> With [[Wilhelm Heinrich Heintz]], he was editor of the ''Zeitschrift für Naturwissenschaften''.<ref>[https://archive.org/details/bub_gb_oqPOAAAAMAAJ Zeitschrift für Naturwissenschaften] Internet Archive</ref>

He is the [[taxonomic authority|taxonomic author]] of the extinct fish genera ''[[Asima]]'' (1848),<ref>[https://www.gbif.org/species/4840444 Asima Giebel, 1848] GBIF</ref> ''[[Elonichthys]]'' (1848),<ref>[https://www.gbif.org/species/4839363 Elonichthys Giebel, 1848] GBIF</ref> and ''Tharsis'' (1847).<ref>[http://taxonomicon.taxonomy.nl/TaxonTree.aspx?src=7229&id=1268839 Taxon: Genus †Tharsis] Taxonomicon</ref><ref>[https://books.google.com/books?id=-S4iAQAAMAAJ&pg=PA233&lpg=PA233&dq=Elonichthys+Christoph+Giebel&source=bl&ots=1Ap0S8Orb3&sig=IQ36qF49jRGSnBLxt3kTXhQy_dU&hl=en&sa=X&ved=0ahUKEwjYxJuOrqbKAhWF4SYKHT5_AcIQ6AEIPjAE#v=onepage&q=Elonichthys%20Christoph%20Giebel&f=false The Genera of Fishes ...: From Linnæus to Cuvier, 1758-1833]  By David Starr Jordan, Barton Warren Evermann</ref>

