{{Refimprove|date=October 2016}} {{Infobox book | image = Great Mambo Chicken and the Transhuman Condition.jpg | <!-- See Wikipedia:WikiProject_Novels or Wikipedia:WikiProject_Books --> | name = Great Mambo Chicken and the Transhuman Condition: Science Slightly over the Edge | author = [[Ed Regis (author)|Ed Regis]] | language = [[English language|English]] | genre = [[Science]] | pages = 320 pp | isbn = 0-201-09258-1 }}
'''''Great Mambo Chicken and the Transhuman Condition''''' is a non-fiction book copyright 1990 by [[Ed Regis (author)|Ed Regis]], an [[United States|American]] author and educator, that presents a lighthearted look at scientific visionaries planning for a future with "post-biological" people,<ref>{{cite journal|url=https://ora.ox.ac.uk/objects/uuid:55ab57ec-70d0-4b93-b058-0d7f57167cc2/datastreams/ATTACHMENT01|title=A History of Transhumanist Thought|author=Nick Bostrom |journal=[[Journal of Evolution and Technology]]|volume=14|date=April 2005}}</ref> [[space colonization]], [[nanotechnology]], and [[cryonics]]. The book emphasizes the personality and projects of [[Robert Truax]], [[Eric Drexler]], [[Gerard K. O'Neill]], [[Chris Langton]], [[Freeman Dyson]], [[Hans Moravec]], [[Ralph Merkle]], [[Robert Forward]], [[Keith Henson]], [[Carolyn Meinel]], [[Gary Hudson (engineer)|Gary Hudson]], [[Saul Kent]], and a number of others.
