{{National parks of Iceland map}} Since 2008, [[Iceland]] has three [[national park]]s.<ref name="visiticeland.com">{{cite web|title=National Parks in Iceland|url=http://www.visiticeland.com/Seedo/NationalParks/|work=Iceland Tourist Board|publisher=Visiticeland.com|accessdate=9 July 2010|deadurl=yes|archiveurl=https://archive.is/20120527080856/http://www.visiticeland.com/Seedo/NationalParks/|archivedate=27 May 2012|df=}}</ref> Prior to 2008 there were four national parks in Iceland; in that year [[Jökulsárgljúfur National Park|Jökulsárgljúfur]] and [[Skaftafell National Park|Skaftafell]] were merged and incorporated into [[Vatnajökull National Park]].<ref name="hi">{{cite web|title=Vatnajokull National Park|url=http://www2.hi.is/page/www.hi.is/haskolasetur_hornafirdi/vatnajokull_nationalpark|work=Háskóli Íslands|publisher=hi.is|accessdate=9 July 2010|deadurl=yes|archiveurl=http://wayback.vefsafn.is/wayback/20090424220646/www2.hi.is/page/www.hi.is/haskolasetur_hornafirdi/vatnajokull_nationalpark|archivedate=24 April 2009|df=}}</ref>
Vatnajökull National Park and Snæfellsjökull National Park are supervised by the [[Ministry for the Environment and Natural Resources (Iceland)|Ministry for the Environment and Natural Resources]], Þingvellir National Park is supervised by the Ministry for the Prime Minister.
